Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This outstanding 74.8ha* landholding is located 40km* south of Perth and 11km* to Rockingham.

Featuring six freehold Certificates of Title, the property has historically operated as a grazing and cropping enterprise and benefits from excellent access, being bordered by the Kwinana Freeway, Mundijong Road, St Albans Road and Pug Road.

The property’s location is within easy access to the City of Rockingham, Kwinana, Baldivis, Mundijong and train services to Mandurah. Perth’s southern corridor has been an outstanding growth region of Western Australia and this property offers a strategic land-banking opportunity.

Zoned “Rural” within the City of Rockingham, this property is in a prime location for future development (STCA).

Offered for immediate sale in one line, by Offers to Purchase closing Wednesday 4 April 2018 at 4pm WST.

*Approximately

CBRE are pleased to offer For Sale 271 Mundijong Road, Baldivis.

This outstanding 14.3* hectare landholding is located only 40* km south of Perth on the Kwinana Freeway, Western Australia.

The property has a portion of infill with screened sand in anticipation of development.

The property’s location is within easy access to the City of Rockingham, Kwinana, Baldivis, Mundijong and train services to Mandurah. Perth’s southern corridor has been an outstanding growth region of Western Australia and this property offers a strategic land-banking opportunity.

Zoned “Rural” within the City of Rockingham this property is being offered for sale via Invitation to Offer. 

For further information on this opportunity, please contact Phil Melville.

*Approximately

CBRE are pleased to offer For Sale 25 Telephone Lane and 20 Lloyd Street Baldivis

The property comprises two titles:
Lot 25 - 66.56 hectares and  
Lot 24 - 8.43 hectares

The property has a brick and tile dwelling with numerous hay sheds, proximity to three phase power, fenced, ample surface water with quality self-mulching clays providing summer feed. 

The property produces cattle, sheep and hay, has two street frontage which gives good access for future businesses and development.

Ground water is available (conditions apply), zoned rural within the City of Rockingham, close to Perth and proximity to Kwinana Freeway make this a compelling buying option for the astute operator/investor.

This property is being offered for Sale via Invitation to Offer.

For further information please contact Phil Melville.

Zoned rural, Lot 9001, Lot 9002 and Lot 9003 are appealing properties ideally suited to Lifestyle, Small business operators and Land bankers. The Lots comprise a combination of low heavy fertile flats, native wetland flora and well-draining sand ridges for potential residential sites. The shallow water table provides plenty of moisture for extended summer grazing and ideal hay paddocks. 

Leary Road is a no through road offering privacy with minimum neighbours and a vista overlooking wetlands.

Lot 9001 has an Optus Communication Tower lease, currently earning $16,300 p/a with a 3% annual increase.

Proximity to Kwinana Freeway and Mundijong Road, located in the southern development growth corridor, offers a rural setting and the option of easy city access.   

The properties have been keenly priced and inspections and further information are available from Phil Melville.
